			<div class="comment-content clearfix">
				<p>The only problem is I do not need a video to look at a bond market chart. Bass is imploding. The Japanese Bonds have not acted according to his script. US Bonds have not acted according to his script. Perhaps one day he may be right and everyone may be wrong. Indeed Japan may stop being a stable economy with low unemployment but not anytime soon. Money talks and Japan prints it&#8217;s own. Investors still regard Japan as a good buy. The stock market is up, the yen is up and the bond rate is as low as ever. Fact is how long will his investors keep throwing money on a losing bet, a bet that is growing losses by the day. He said short Japanese bonds-Fail, His results on the yen, the stock market have all been wrong. Watching a video written and promoting a idealogical meme means nothing. Where the market is, what it is likely and has been doing count. Kyle Bass has made lots of people a lot of money. Problem for him it has been those who bet against him. What will those investors who have made a boatload do once the Market switches (if ever), offload their holdings and change side with little loss incurred. He has bet against the market and is losing badly and until he starts to recover the market will keep taking his money (well his investors)</p>
				
